Should you need accessible assistance in the general admission section, please visit a Guest Services kiosk after entering the venue for relocation to the accessible section of the lawn. Beach style are OK and rental chairs are available. • No laser pointers • Empty plastic drinking water containers will be allowed in. One factory sealed water bottles of 20 oz. size will be allowed in. Sorry, no factory sealed soda bottles please. • Food in clear plastic gallon sized bag (one per patron) will also be allowed in. No large, hard-shelled coolers or ice chests. • School-size or small backpacks are normally allowed in, but may be subject to change at the artists request. All bags are subject to visual search. NO Large Backpacks. • Emergency medical personnel and ambulance transport is on site. Camera Policy: Personal cameras are allowed in the venue. generalInfo.childRule: Children under the age of 2 are free in General Admission Lawn seating. Every one including Children will require a reserved ticket to access the reserved seating area. All ages are allowed inside the amphitheatre.

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: THE ORCHID SHOW HOURS February 24-March 31: 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. (Tuesdays through Sundays) April 1-April 8: 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. (Tuesdays through Sundays) Last admission to the Conservatory is 90 minutes before closing.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Located in the Visitor Center (Conservatory gate entrance) and Mosholu gate (Metro-North entrance) Customer must present the actual credit card used to place the order, a photo I.D., and the order number.

venues.parkingDetail: Parking is on a first-come, first-served basis. The Garden is easy to reach by Metro-North or subway. On-site self parking (Tuesdays-Sundays): $10 per vehicle On-site valet parking (Saturdays & Sundays): $15 per vehicle
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Garden facilities are accessible. Patrons requesting accessible seating may purchase and use a regular ticket. - Wheelchairs are available free of charge at both Garden entrances, on a first-come, first-served basis (reservations are not accepted). An ID must be left with Visitor Services. - The Garden, its buildings, and its tour vehicles are accessible. However, portions of the Rock and Native Plant Gardens, Home Gardening Center, and Forest may be inaccessible due to rocky, muddy, and/or narrow paths. - Audiotours, which are t-switch compatible, are available at the Conservatory and Visitor Center for no additional charge. - A tour of a Garden collection with an American Sign Language interpreter is given the third Saturday of every month. Please call 718-817-8700 for more information. - Sight-enabling guide dogs/animals are permitted. - Accessible parking spots are reserved throughout the parking areas. - Accessible strollers for children are permitted in the Conservatory. *For additional information, contact Visitor Services at 718-817-8649.

generalInfo.generalRule: GARDEN ETIQUETTE Please remember the following Garden guidelines: - Stay on paths. - Deposit trash in designated receptacles. - Do not pick flowers or climb trees. - Pets are not allowed, except sight-enabling guide dogs/animals. - Picnic only in the designated picnic area. - No strollers, tripods, or easels in the Conservatory. - Shirts and shoes are required at all times. - No fires, alcohol, or portable radios. - Recreational sports, including skating, ball playing, cycling, etc., are no permitted. *Smoking is prohibited in: all buildings; the Forest; Children's Adventure Garden and Family Garden; Rock and Native Plant Gardens; Conservatory courtyards; and public Tram Tour and all other Garden tour vehicles. We ask that visitors do not smoke in the outdoor portions of the cafes or when participating in a public walking tour. *Smoking is permitted in all other outdoor areas.
generalInfo.childRule: Admission is free for children under the age of 2.

name: Mad Arts
description:
Mad Arts

We are a creative hub that stimulates the senses and engages the mind. A celebration of the limitless imagination that resides within us all.

Mad Arts showcases artists, designers, and creatives whose work disrupts, provokes, and transforms what art and technology can achieve, seeking to close the gap between the artist and viewer to expand digital horizons. 

This year, Mad Arts is ready for a new level of experiential artwork driven by emerging technologies. The opening of the new permanent home in Dania Beach marks a watershed moment for South Florida in a 50,000 sq ft building dedicated to showcasing and exploring immersive art, digital technologies, and outdoor activations. Boasting an outdoor garden and more than triple the current gallery space, the expansion enables Mad Arts to present an ambitious tech-driven program.  

The opening will have more than twenty exhibitions from a diverse range of artistic voices and perspectives across the arts and technology sectors on a local, national, and international level.  



Mad Arts Hours of Operation: 
Monday: Closed
Tuesday: Closed
Wednesday: Closed
Thursday: 10AM–10PM
Friday: 10AM–10PM
Saturday: 10AM–10PM
Sunday: 10AM–10PM

Tickets are also available for purchase on-site and are valid for any day and time within the museum's operating hours. Free guided tours are available upon request.
